IMPORTANT — effect on the compiled assembly
-------------------------------------------
Because the protocol layer is LGPL-3.0, the produced assembly
(EasilyNET.Drivers.S7Plus.dll) as a whole must be conveyed in compliance with
the LGPL-3.0 terms. In particular, recipients must be able to relink/replace the
LGPL-covered portion. The MIT grant above applies only to the three wrapper
files listed in (1); it does not relax the LGPL obligations of the protocol
layer. When you only reference the prebuilt NuGet package as a library
dependency (dynamic linking), the LGPL is generally satisfied by retaining these
notices and pointing users to the corresponding source.

